thread.title: Clay Matthews to Kaepernick: 'You ain't Russell Wilson, bro'
thread.title_full: Clay Matthews to Kaepernick: 'You ain't Russell Wilson, bro'

author: AMARA GRAUTSKI
title: Clay Matthews to Kaepernick: 'You ain't Russell Wilson, bro'
text:
Share this URL 
Colin Kaepernick first got sacked by Clay Matthews, then got taunted. 
The Packers linebacker drove the 49ers quarterback into the ground in the third quarter, and then in the fourth yelled at Kaepernick, "You ain't Russell Wilson, bro," during Green Bay's 17-3 victory over San Francisco. 
Kaepernick went 13-for-25 with 160 passing yards and an interception. He rushed for 57 yards on 10 carries. 
After the third-quarter sack, Matthews also mocked Kaepernick by performing his biceps-kissing celebration. Ezra Shaw/Getty Images Packers linebacker Clay Matthews sacks Niners QB Colin Kaepernick. 
The Packer said after the game that the move was harmless but didn't mention the Wilson putdown. 
"Nah, it's not planned," Matthews said. "I was going to hit him with the predator, and then I had a light bulb go off in my head. It's just having fun. We're a bunch of kids out there running around and having fun at each other's expense." 
Meanwhile, the Seahawks quarterback takes on the Lions at 8:30 p.m. on Monday. Related Stories
